Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "smeju" in different forms and positions:

1. Oni *smeju* se zajedno u parku. (They are laughing together in the park.)
2. Ja se *smejem* tvojim šalama. (I'm laughing at your jokes.)
3. Kada bih imao više novca, *smejao* bih se svaki dan. (If I had more money, I would laugh every day.)
4. Oni *smiju* da dođu sa nama na večeru. (They are allowed to come with us for dinner.)
5. Ti se *smiješ* kao da znaš nešto što ja ne znam. (You're smiling as if you know something I don't.)
6. Kada čujem tu pesmu, uvek se *nasmejem*. (Whenever I hear that song, I always laugh.)
7. Da li se ti *smiješ* mom šalu? (Are you laughing at my joke?)
8. Ne *smijemo* dozvoliti da se to ponovi. (We must not allow that to happen again.)

Note: The word "smeju" is written with the Serbian Latin alphabet as "smeju" and with the Serbian Cyrillic alphabet as "смеју".